  "text": "Grab your scarf — this one had EVERYTHING! Quarter-final, 12 July 2026, Kansas City — and Argentina outlasted Switzerland in extra time to set up a blockbuster semi-final with England. The champions were made to work deep into extra time by a Swiss side riding the high of their shootout heroics.\n\n10' — Alexis Mac Allister buried it, 1–0! 68' — Dan Ndoye lashed it home, 1–1! 114' — Julián Álvarez made no mistake, 2–1! 121' — Lautaro Martínez found the net, 3–1!\n\nAlexis Mac Allister headed in a Messi corner early, twice left unmarked and punishing it the second time. Dan Ndoye levelled with a tight-angle finish after a neat one-two, and Switzerland dug in for extra time. Then Julián Álvarez unleashed a wonderful strike from distance in the 112th minute, and Lautaro Martínez added late gloss to seal it. Argentina keep finding another gear when the tie demands it — the mark of a team that knows how to win these.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nThe neutrals were on their feet; nobody in the building sat still.\n\nFULL-TIME: Argentina 3–1 Switzerland! Argentina march on, Switzerland head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
